<title>dispatch</title>
<link rel="shortcut icon" href="https://old.comicserver.org/img/sum logo.png" />
<div class="mydiv" id="myDiv" style="border:1px solid var(--ba);border-radius:5px;margin:center;width:50%;color:var(--bt)">
<title>dispatch</title>
<p style="padding: 10px"><h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:Emblema One;color:var(--ba)">sign into dispatch</h1>
<form action="/login/password" method="post">
    <section>
        <input id="username" name="username" placeholder="Username" style="width:100%;text-align:center;color:var(--ba)" type="text" autocomplete="username" required autofocus>
    </section>
    <section>
        <input id="current-password" placeholder="Password" name="password" style="width:100%;text-align:center;color:var(--ba)" type="password" autocomplete="current-password" required>
    </section>
    <button class="button" id="signinbutton" style="color:var(--ba)" type="submit">Sign in</button>
</form>
<p style="padding: 10px;color:var(--ba)">dispatch is a companion website to the long standing ComicServer project. dispatch brings extra functionality that doesn't quite fit with ComicServer and builds on MuncieUI to bring a more refined experience for those wanting more than just comics.</p>
<br>
<br>
<i style="padding-left: 10px;padding-right: 10px;color:var(--ba)">Last Updated with dispatch one (v1.0.0, v2023.01.29)</i>
</div>
<style>
body {
  display:flex;
  margin:0;
  flex-direction:column;
}

.mydiv {
  margin:auto;
}
</style>
<script>
if( /Android|webOS|iPhone|iPod|BlackBerry|IEMobile|Opera Mini/i.test(navigator.userAgent) ) {
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.width = "100%"
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.fontSize = "5vw"
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.border = "none"
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.overflow = "hidden"
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.color = "var(--batext)"
document.getElementById('current-password').style.color = "var(--batext)"
document.getElementById('username').style.color = "var(--batext)"
document.getElementById('myDiv').style.padding = "10px"
document.getElementById('current-password').style.fontSize = "5vw"
document.getElementById('username').style.fontSize = "5vw"
document.getElementById('signinbutton').style.fontSize = "4vw"
}
</script>
<%- include('theme') %>
</div>